	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> <date>August 26<hi rend="sup">th</hi>. Elul 5<hi rend="sup">th</hi>. 5598</date></p>
				<p>Dear Uncle.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><date>Sabbath</date> is just over and being at <persName>Mr Allens</persName><lb/> when <persName>Mrs. E. Moses</persName> &#38; other friends are assembled&#44; I have<lb/> resolved to scratch a few lines by way of accompaniment<lb/> to the two sermons I send by her.  One I deliver&#39;d on<lb/> <add>Hebrew</add> and the Men today and was composed during the past<lb/> week on <date>Tuesday</date> <date>Wednesday</date> &#38; <date>Thursday</date>.  The are con&#45;<lb/>nected and are a continuation of the Election of <placeName>Israel</placeName><lb/> in the printed book vol. 2&#44; and I believe the 2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> &#38; 4th<lb/> thereof.  I hope they will please you&#59; yet I fear your<lb/> partiality makes you attach value to things of mine<lb/> which otherwise may deserve but little commendation.<lb/>  As I intend probably to continue the subject I would thank<lb/> you to send them back by an early opportunity.  I intend<lb/> going to <placeName>N. York</placeName> in the morning&#44; but if the weather<lb/> remains as intensely hot as it has been today I may<lb/> possibly defer my starting.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Please to console <persName>Aunt R</persName> and <persName>Rachel</persName> on the<lb/> death of <persName>Mr. M. Judah</persName>&#59; I know he has not been<lb/> in communication with you for some time&#44; still I have<lb/> no doubt his sudden death will cause him to be<lb/> regretted by those so nearly connected with th<add>&#63;</add> him.<lb/>  May the Lord send his consolation to them to preserve</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>them from further affliction.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Let me have a letter from you by <date>Thursday</date> evening when I<lb/> intend being back again at this place&#44; God willing.  As there<lb/> has been but a few Mendaner<add>&#63;</add> at Synagogue during the sum&#45;<lb/>mer I have delivered no discourses&#44; as I do not like to speak<lb/> to empty benches.  Thinking that today many would be there I<lb/> wrote during the week&#59; but the attendance today was bad enough<lb/> This is no great encouragement&#59; but I have never waited for<lb/> this much&#44; so I am never<add>&#63;</add> much disappointed.</p>
				<p>Wishing you much health happiness</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I remain</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Your obt. nephew</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">Isaac Leeser</persName></p>
				<p><persName>Mrs. Moses</persName> will give you all<lb/> the floating talk if there is any&#44; which I doubt.<lb/> My love to all friends.</p>
		</body>
